 Patton  Connecticut College  Dr  William I  Hitchcock  University of Virginia  10 00   10 20 am   Break 10 30 am   12 00 pm   Panel Five The Reagan Legacy  Chair  Dr  Richard Bidlack  Washington and Lee University  Dr  Beth Fisher  University of Toronto  Dr  Archie Brown  Oxford University 12 00 pm  Closing Remarks  12 15 pm  No Host Lunch at the Sheridan Livery Inn  35 N  Main St  Lexington  VA 1 30 pm  Optional Tour of VMI Post  gathering at Jackson Memorial Hall   VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu VMI   CLE    The Enduring Legacy  Program  skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid 